message.content: cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.CR. The paper focuses on the completeness of argumentative steps necessary to conclude effectiveness of an algorithm in the machine learning and artificial intelligence literature, specifically in the area of supervised learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
